        <table id="t08290142">
            <title>Park Brake Switch Circuits Voltage Check Chart</title>
            <tgroup cols="3">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="1.70in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="1.60in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="3.24in"/>
                <spanspec namest="2" nameend="4" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="4" spanname="S1T6"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T6" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Diagnostic Trouble Codes</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>70 14 1 0</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN1" align="center">
                            <para>Air Powered Park Brake is stuck.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>70 14 1 1</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN1" align="center">
                            <para>The auto apply portion with the Air Powered Park Brake is not operating.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>639 14 241 254</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN1" align="center">
                            <para>Full Power Brake information not communicating to the ESC.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T6">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Park Brake Switch Connector (1813) or (1815) Voltage Checks</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>Check with Brake Switch Disconnected and the Ignition Key "On"</para>
                            <note>
                                <para>Always check connectors for damage and pushed-out terminals.</para>
                            </note>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" align="center">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>(1104) harness connector, cavity C or (1107) cavity B to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>If voltage is incorrect, check circuits A44BB or A44CC for open or short circuits. If
                                circuits check good voltage is missing from ESC connector (1600) pin 32.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>(1104) harness connector, cavity C or (1107) cavity B to (1104) cavity D or (1107)
                                cavity A.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>If voltage is correct and condition still exists, the brake switch has failed. Replace
                                brake switch.
                            </para>
                            <para>If voltage is incorrect, check circuit A9B, A9K, A9C or A9H for an open circuit or
                                good connection to ground.
                            </para>
                            <para>If no open circuits are found, check system controller connector (1600) pin 3 for zero
                                volt reference signal.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T6">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">There are no diagnostic trouble codes associated with the park brake
                                    switch.
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
